==English==
===Etymology===
From [[observe]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/əb'zɜ:və/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|observers}}
#A person who [[adhere]]s or [[follow]]s laws, guidelines, etc.
#:''I shall be an '''observer''' of the local customs.''
# anyone who [[watch]]es, [[monitor]]s or takes notice
#:''Most impartial '''observers''' agreed that Sampras had not served well.''
#A person sent, as a [[delegate]], to a [[meeting]] or other [[function]] to [[monitor]] but not to [[participate]]
#:''The UN sent many '''observers''' to the country's first elections.''
#(''military'') A [[crew]] [[member]] on an [[aircraft]] who makes [[observation]]s of enemy positions or aircraft
#:''The only crew-member to survive the crash was the Canadian '''observer'''.''
#(''military'') A [[sentry]] etc manning an [[observation post]]
#:''We waited till dusk when the '''observers'''' vision was poorest.''

